FBIS4-14265 "drnes083_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-083 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 India Congress-I Spokesman Comments on NPT Congress-I Spokesman Comments on NPT BK2904040094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 28 Apr 94 BK2904040094 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The Congress-I has said that India will not sign the Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT] unless all countries are included in it and it becomes nondiscriminatory in character. Talking to newspersons in New Delhi today, the party spokesman, Mr. V.N. Gadgil, said revision of the treaty is due next year and, therefore, member countries need to have some negotiations in this regard.
